{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-86e850fd60634276", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# MaskGCT: Zero-Shot Text-to-Speech with Masked Generative Codec Transformer\narXiv: 2409.00750\nAuthors: Yuancheng Wang, Haoyue Zhan, Liwei Liu, Ruihong Zeng, Haotian Guo, Jiachen Zheng, Qiang Zhang, Xueyao Zhang, Shunsi Zhang, Zhizheng Wu\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Proposes MaskGCT, a fully non-autogressive text-to-speech system that eliminates the need for explicit text-speech alignment supervision and phone-level duration prediction.\n  2. Introduces a two-stage masked generative transformer framework consisting of a text-to-semantic model and a semantic-to-acoustic model.\n  3. Trains a VQ-VAE on speech self-supervised learning representations to extract discrete semantic tokens, minimizing information loss compared to traditional k-means quantization.\n  4. Achieves human-level or state-of-the-art performance in zero-shot TTS regarding speech quality, similarity, and intelligibility on multiple benchmarks.\n  5. Demonstrates scalability to diverse speech generation tasks, including cross-lingual dubbing, emotion control, speech content editing, and voice conversion.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Transformer, TTS/控制-参考语音, TTS/功能-多说话人, TTS/功能-语音编辑\n===MaskGCT===\n# F5-TTS: A Fairytaler that Fakes Fluent and Faithful Speech with Flow Matching\narXiv: 2410.06885\nAuthors: Yushen Chen, Zhikang Niu, Ziyang Ma, Keqi Deng, Chunhui Wang, Jian Zhao, Kai Yu, Xie Chen\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: reading\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introduces F5-TTS, a fully non-autoregressive text-to-speech system based on flow matching with a Diffusion Transformer (DiT) that eliminates the need for complex designs like duration models, text encoders, and phoneme alignment.\n  2. Improves text-speech alignment and model robustness by leveraging ConvNeXt V2 blocks to refine text representation before concatenation with speech features.\n  3. Proposes an inference-time Sway Sampling strategy for flow steps that significantly enhances generation performance and efficiency without requiring model retraining.\n  4. Achieves faster training and a highly efficient inference Real-Time Factor (RTF) of 0.15, outperforming existing state-of-the-art diffusion-based TTS models.\n  5. Demonstrates highly natural and expressive zero-shot ability, seamless code-switching capability, and speed control efficiency when trained on a public 100K hours multilingual dataset.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Flow, TTS/功能-DiT, TTS/功能-多语言, TTS/控制-参考语音, TTS/功能-快速生成\n===F5-TTS===\n# CosyVoice 2: Scalable Streaming Speech Synthesis with Large Language Models\narXiv: 2412.10117\nAuthors: Zhihao Du, Yuxuan Wang, Qian Chen, Xian Shi, Xiang Lv, Tianyu Zhao, Zhifu Gao, Yexin Yang, Changfeng Gao, Hui Wang, Fan Yu, Huadai Liu, Zhengyan Sheng, Yue Gu, Chong Deng, Wen Wang, Shiliang Zhang, Zhijie Yan, Jingren Zhou\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introducing CosyVoice 2, a scalable streaming speech synthesis model that integrates large language models with a speech decoder.\n  2. Designing a unified architecture that seamlessly supports both streaming and non-streaming speech synthesis.\n  3. Developing a large language model equipped with block-wise causal attention to effectively balance lookahead context and streaming latency.\n  4. Implementing a modified finite scalar quantization strategy with an adaptive weight to achieve high-compression and high-accuracy speech tokenization.\n  5. Demonstrating through comprehensive experiments that the proposed model significantly outperforms its predecessor and achieves state-of-the-art performance in speech synthesis.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/功能-流式, TTS/功能-多语言, TTS/控制-参考语音\n===CosyVoice2===\n# Seed-TTS: A Family of High-Quality Versatile Speech Generation Models\narXiv: 2406.02430\nAuthors: Philip Anastassiou, Jiawei Chen, Jitong Chen, Yuanzhe Chen, Zhuo Chen, Ziyi Chen, Jian Cong, Lelai Deng, Chuang Ding, Lu Gao, Mingqing Gong, Peisong Huang, Qingqing Huang, Zhiying Huang, Yuanyuan Huo, Dongya Jia, Chumin Li, Feiya Li, Hui Li, Jiaxin Li, Xiaoyang Li, Xingxing Li, Lin Liu, Shouda Liu, Sichao Liu, Xudong Liu, Yuchen Liu, Zhengxi Liu, Lu Lu, Junjie Pan, Xin Wang, Yuping Wang, Yuxuan Wang, Zhen Wei, Jian Wu, Chao Yao, Yifeng Yang, Yuanhao Yi, Junteng Zhang, Qidi Zhang, Shuo Zhang, Wenjie Zhang, Yang Zhang, Zilin Zhao, Dejian Zhong, Xiaobin Zhuang\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We introduce Seed-TTS, a family of speech generation models capable of generating highly expressive, human-like speech with state-of-the-art performance in multiple evaluations.\n  2. We present a novel self-distillation extension of Seed-TTS for timbre disentanglement and demonstrate state-of-the-art performance in the voice conversion task.\n  3. We introduce a novel reinforcement learning-based post-training extension for Seed-TTS that holistically improves the model's performance.\n  4. We present a novel fully diffusion-based variant of Seed-TTS that achieves superior generation quality and demonstrates advantages in speech editing.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/架构-NAR-Diffusion, TTS/功能-DiT, TTS/功能-RL优化, TTS/控制-参考语音, TTS/功能-语音编辑, TTS/功能-多说话人\n===SeedTTS===", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "45ed3ed8-8c6d-4e56-8ce3-53ab0e12fc21", "uuid": "d68c9050-add5-4d32-9617-e2ed05c56eab", "timestamp": "2026-07-23T07:09:45.600Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# MaskGCT: Zero-Shot Text-to-Speech with Masked Generative Codec Transformer\narXiv: 2409.00750\nAuthors: Yuancheng Wang, Haoyue Zhan, Liwei Liu, Ruihong Zeng, Haotian Guo, Jiachen Zheng, Qiang Zhang, Xueyao Zhang, Shunsi Zhang, Zhizheng Wu\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Proposes MaskGCT, a fully non-autogressive text-to-speech system that eliminates the need for explicit text-speech alignment supervision and phone-level duration prediction.\n  2. Introduces a two-stage masked generative transformer framework consisting of a text-to-semantic model and a semantic-to-acoustic model.\n  3. Trains a VQ-VAE on speech self-supervised learning representations to extract discrete semantic tokens, minimizing information loss compared to traditional k-means quantization.\n  4. Achieves human-level or state-of-the-art performance in zero-shot TTS regarding speech quality, similarity, and intelligibility on multiple benchmarks.\n  5. Demonstrates scalability to diverse speech generation tasks, including cross-lingual dubbing, emotion control, speech content editing, and voice conversion.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-NAR-Transformer, TTS/控制-参考语音, TTS/功能-多说话人, TTS/功能-语音编辑\n===MaskGCT===\n# F5-TTS: A Fairytaler that Fakes Fluent and Faithful Speech with Flow Matching\narXiv: 2410.06885\nAuthors: Yushen Chen, Zhikang Niu, Ziyang Ma, Keqi Deng, Chunhui Wang, Jian Zhao, Kai Yu, Xie Chen\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: reading\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introduces F5-TTS, a fully non-autoregressive text-to-speech system based on flow matching with a Diffusion Transformer (DiT) that eliminates the need for complex designs like duration models, text encoders, and phoneme alignment.\n  2. Improves text-speech alignment and model robustness by leveraging ConvNeXt V2 blocks to refine text representation before concatenation with speech features.\n  3. Proposes an inference-time Sway Sampling strategy for flow steps that significantly enhances generation performance and efficiency without requiring model retraining.\n  4. Achieves faster training and a highly efficient inference Real-Time Factor (RTF) of 0.15, outperforming existing state-of-the-art diffusion-based TTS models.\n  5. Demonstrates highly natural and expressive zero-shot ability, seamless code-switching capability, and speed control efficiency w